history.content: We don't wait to enroll already declared majors for new majors to be processed if gsi hiring has been completed.  As it says elsewhere on piazza, we are working on expanding cs170.  We will be able to do so before the end of phase 2. (the lecture size has already been expanded but there may not be time to add new discussion sections today so that will happen either this Sunday or on January 3, 4 or 5).  Keep your eyes open for that and drop and re-add to one of the new discussions before January 8th and you should be able to enroll ahead of non-majors. (If all major processing hasn't happened by January 8th, we will likely delay opening the floodgates to non-majors until that process has been completed.)

Does anyone know what happened with CS170 and why the waitlist was processed already? A counselor told me that intended CS majors who applied this semester would get priority over non-CS majors currently on the waitlist, but it turns out all discussions are currently full.

Thanks!
history.subject: CS170 Update?
